##Dictation | 4:30 am, I first received the "Blue Sky Warrior" Xu Peng's accident call

Micro Signal Xinminzhoukan

Function description, depth and angle —— this is what we can do.

Many people compare Xu Peng to a hero, in fact, there has never been a superhero, are tens of millions of ordinary people to come forward, with their own flesh and blood body to carry the gate of darkness, put us into the light.

Dictation | Cai Chao

Tidying | Wu Xue

At 4:30 a.m. on February 21st, I'll never forget this moment.

That day, there was no light and no moon. The Rain pattered on the windshield of my car. After loading and unloading a batch of supplies, I took a short break in a tin shed outside the Wuhan Warehouse, which receives donations from around the world, it's run by Blue Sky Rescue and the China Charity Association. My identity is the Blue Sky Rescue Team Wuhan Emergency Warehouse Jiangsu Area Leader Cai Chao.

Half Asleep, I suddenly received a call from my teammate Ni Rongkai, the other end of the phone came a burst of hysterical crying: "quickly save people, quickly save people, Big Ben is dying... " I heard, the brain was momentarily confused. From Ni Rongkai's sobbing, I heard "Big Ben" , that is, Blue Sky Rescue Team Captain Xu Peng, in Shandong transport medical supplies, an accident.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Blue Sky Rescue Team Wuhan Emergency Warehouse Jiangsu Area Leader Cai Chao (middle) map | respondents

The sound of crying on the other end of the phone is extremely harsh in the silence of the night in Wuhan. In panic, I steady God son, on the one hand let Ni Rongkai hurriedly dial 120 rescue, on the other hand let him report the location of my accident. The whole time, I could feel my lip quiver. Putting down the phone, I threw on a few clothes, grabbed my jacket and rushed out of the Tin House. I trotted to the warehouse leader's car, where I gasped for air.

Xu and I go way back, and when we first met in 2016 during the Funing storm, he was carrying and distributing supplies for hours on end. Look at the appearance of cool tough guy image, tied a small pigtail, but the bones are silent, especially low-key people. Over the past four years, we have met on different "relief battlefields" such as Laos, Myanmar and Yushu snow disaster. On February 7, he took the initiative to drive a car to support Wuhan and distribute supplies to major hospitals at an emergency warehouse, we also forged a deep "revolutionary friendship" .

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Xu Peng (first left) and Cai Chao (first right) rescue in Yushu, Qinghai

I was the first person to get a call about the accident, and I couldn't leave him hanging like that. At that time my mind was too chaotic, made a very calm decision: "out of the city, to Shandong. " The accident that day is the 16th day of the city of Wuhan, want to out of the city easy. Our cars have special passes for trans-shipment, so they can get on the highway, but it's against the law if we don't report it, and I don't care. I'm out of control. At 5.30 am, one of my teammates and I jumped into the cab and started the car, which was diverted to the accident site in Liangping County, Shandong Province.

Along the way, I had movie flashbacks of the rescue with Big Ben. I was too scared to answer the phone on the highway for fear of bad news. I drove and cried, 200 miles in two hours, but it felt like a century. The car went faster and faster, but my mind began to come to its senses, and I asked myself: If you get off the highway, you have to be in isolation for 14 days, not only doesn't it help, it makes it worse. What's the point? I decided to turn back to Wuhan at once.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The Blue Sky rescue team has to sign a release slip for every mission

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Xu Peng eats instant noodles

I began to contact Captain Qiu, the leader of the team in Jining, Shandong Province, to ask for his help. Captain Qiu had already arrived at the scene of the accident by tacit agreement. At 5:20, he got into an ambulance with Big Ben and arrived at the hospital. The hospital said it would do anything to save people... but the most frightening thing came. Xu Peng's 39-year-old life was forever fixed on this rainy night in the spring of 2020. The strength I was holding in my heart gave out.

From the description of my teammate Ni Rongkai, who was transporting supplies together, I learned the whole process of Xu Peng's accident. Xu Peng participated in rescue activities for five or six years of experience, has long been accustomed to long-distance driving, his usual physical quality is very good, know that day at 12 o'clock in the evening there was an urgent task of transporting 100 killing machines, deliberately in the afternoon to sleep for more than 3 hours. At 4:30 on the morning of the 21st, Xu Peng and his party drove one kilometer to the Liangshan Service area in jining city, Shandong Province. Suddenly, a truck stopped in the middle of the road at the center of a high-speed highway, the truck driver turned off his lights and fell asleep, thinking the traffic wouldn't clear for a while.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Xu Peng carries supplies and supplies | interviewee

Unexpectedly, the truck in front of me drove away. Only the truck was parked in the driveway, and there was no sign to turn on the lights. The rescue party altogether three vehicles, the first is the minivan, a sharp turn fortunately avoided. The second car is Xu Peng driving the pickup truck, did not have time to turn the steering wheel, immediately out of control, straight into the belly of the truck.

Teammate Ni Rongkai was driving the third car. It was raining nonstop that day. Ten seconds before the accident, he had just used his walkie-talkie to alert the two teammates in front of him: "there is a traffic jam in front of us. Please be careful. " As soon as he spoke, the car crashed. After he stopped, ... Ni Rongkai rushed to the rescue, and then 119 rescue workers, 120 ambulances came to the rescue...

Xu Peng is the rescue team captain, is the mobile team "Ruyi Jingu Bang, " but rescue, we never ask each other identity and each other's home things. After Xu's death, it took a lot of work to find his family back home in Yancheng, his wife, his 10-year-old son and his elderly mother. In the early hours of the next day, Xu's body was returned to Suzhou, Jiangsu Province, for a memorial service before returning to his hometown in Yancheng for burial.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Photo of Xu Peng's work permit | interviewees

Video source | Suzhou Radio and television station crab video

Along the way, through the high-speed mouth, service area, hundreds of teammates, traffic police, strangers, spontaneously lined up, facing the hearse solemn salute, farewell... .... This spontaneous departure has been repeated a dozen times on the 350 km journey from Shouguang in Shandong Province to Yancheng in Jiangsu province. That day, my teammates and I, in the emergency warehouse in Wuhan, watching the video reported on the phone, crying. I feel very sad, sad is only through the screen to Xu Peng to say goodbye forever.

Although Xu Peng is 2 years younger than me, but he is more like a big brother, work down-to-earth, hard-working, reporting good news to family members but not bad news. These days, even with all the stress of the rescue, I still keep flashing images of the previous rescue. Remember last year when the Yuanxiao Festival was hit by snow in Yushu, we went to the rescue and stayed there for more than 20 days at a time. At that time, Yushu was in very difficult conditions. Our village was over 5,400 meters above sea level. We all carried sleeping bags on our backs and slept in the open air. We struggled day and night for days, i'm almost exhausted.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The village where Yushu was rescued is 5,400 meters above sea level

Xu Peng is usually versatile, guitar, singing, composition and lyrics, play very well. He himself communicated with the Tibetans and composed an original song, which he sang to them. Another time, the rescue team's car got stuck in a river channel, and the physical work on the plateau was very laborious. Xu Peng was the first to rush ahead to hammer and hammer the nails Xu Peng is gone, but the new coronavirus is not the same as human emotional animals, it did not leave time for us to grieve, we only put the strength in the rescue. At present, dozens of Blue Sky Rescue Team members, take turns to take over the unfinished work of Xu Peng.

Xu Peng sings for everyone

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Xu Peng carries supplies for the victims

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
2010 Yushu earthquake was the first to rush to the rescue when the vehicle got stuck in a river

Blue Sky rescue team has more than 170 teammates across the country, they and Xu Peng, like every day there is work, has not stopped the pace. I know you've sent me a lot of messages, and I haven't responded. Because a lot of busy rescue scene, simply too late to send and receive Wechat, water and electricity is often cut. The night you contacted me for the interview, I arrived at the tin shed at 11:30, and when I answered the phone, I was too tired to talk, I just wanted to fall asleep, so the interview was postponed to the next day, and in the one hour interview, my walkie-talkie went off more than five or six times.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Cai Chao and his teammates are checking supplies for the interviewees

If you ask me, during the rescue in Wuhan, which dates, what did. More often than not, I simply don't have the spare brain power or energy to think. Our rescue workers slept in their cars, ate instant noodles and worked all night long, but they were nothing compared to the medical staff. One time, a docking person from a hospital in Wuhan came to the warehouse to pick up the goods and begged us, "can you give us some more N95 masks? Our hospital is very short of them. " Because the material donations were all directed to designated hospitals, we really wanted to give them at that time, but as executors, we don't get to assign.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A few days before the incident, Xu Peng in Wuhan Tianhe Airport deployment of supplies for the map | respondents

As she spoke, the receiver burst into tears. She said the hospital really needs N95 masks. Disposable masks are too risky for first-line medical care. I felt bad and had mixed feelings. I promised her that I would help them find a way to coordinate a batch of N95 masks. If I couldn't, I would ask my superiors to give them their own N95 masks. And such helplessness, in Wuhan may occur every day, before the epidemic, we are too difficult, but we are holding that strength.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On February 10, Xu Peng's last friend circle

Xu Peng died on duty for the fifth day, every night when I can not sleep, I will look at a screen and his chat records. "Be a good boy, daddy will go to Wuhan to fight monsters! " Xu Peng explained to his 10-year-old Son why he was not at home with a beautiful lie on Feb. 10. Many people compare Xu Peng to a hero, in fact, there has never been a superhero, are tens of millions of ordinary people to come forward, with their own flesh and blood body to carry the gate of darkness, put us into the light.
